To write and deploy a simple smart contract using Solidity in Remix IDE, interact with the contract functions, and observe how each interaction generates a transaction on the blockchain.

1.	In the File Explorer, click on “+” (New File) and name it:
SimpleStorage.sol
----------------------------------------------------
// SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT
pragma solidity ^0.8.0;

// A simple smart contract to store and retrieve a number
contract SimpleStorage {
    uint256 private number;

    // Event to log updates
    event NumberUpdated(uint256 oldValue, uint256 newValue, address updatedBy);

    // Function to update the stored number
    function setNumber(uint256 _number) public {
        uint256 old = number;
        number = _number;
        emit NumberUpdated(old, _number, msg.sender);
    }

    // Function to read the stored number
    function getNumber() public view returns (uint256) {
        return number;
    }
}
---------------------------------------------------------


3. Click Compile SimpleStorage.sol

4. After successful compilation, go to the DEPLOY & RUN TRANSACTIONS tab:
•	Set Environment to JavaScript VM (Prauge)
•	Make sure SimpleStorage is selected under Contract
•	Click Deploy

5. After deployment:
•	The contract instance will appear under Deployed Contracts
•	Expand it to see the functions
    To interact:
•	Click getNumber → view default value (usually 0)
•	Enter a value in setNumber (e.g., 10) and click the button
•	Observe:
o	A new transaction entry appears in the Transactions panel
o	Click the transaction to view gas used, status, logs, and events
